<cite id="CITEREFSchmitzWalker2004" class="citation journal cs1">Schmitz, David F.; Walker, Vanessa (2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/24914773">"Jimmy Carter and the Foreign Policy of Human Rights: The Development of a Post-Cold War Foreign Policy"</a>. <i>Diplomatic History</i>. <b>28</b> (1): <span class="nowrap">113–</span>143. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1111%2Fj.1467-7709.2004.00400.x">10.1111/j.1467-7709.2004.00400.x</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISSN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISSN (identifier)">ISSN</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://search.worldcat.org/issn/0145-2096">0145-2096</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/24914773">24914773</a>. <q>The call to overcome the nation's 'inordinate fear of communism' was not, [Brzezinski]  wrote, 'a dismissal of the reality of Soviet power but an optimistic recognition of the greater appeal of liberty and of the superiority of the democratic system.'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span></q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Diplomatic+History&amp;rft.atitle=Jimmy+Carter+and+the+Foreign+Policy+of+Human+Rights%3A+The+Development+of+a+Post-Cold+War+Foreign+Policy&amp;rft.volume=28&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=113-143&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.issn=0145-2096&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F24914773%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-7709.2004.00400.x&amp;rft.aulast=Schmitz&amp;rft.aufirst=David+F.&amp;rft.au=Walker%2C+Vanessa&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F24914773&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AZbigniew+Brzezinski" class="Z3988"